{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:sirach.34",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 34,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 34 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.34.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:1",
      "text": "Vain and false hopes are for a man void of understanding. Dreams give wings to fools.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.34.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:2",
      "text": "As one who grasps at a shadow and follows after the wind, so is he who sets his mind on dreams.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.34.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:3",
      "text": "The vision of dreams is a reflection, the likeness of a face near a face.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.34.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:4",
      "text": "From an unclean thing what can be cleansed? From that which is false what can be true?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.34.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:5",
      "text": "Divinations, and soothsayings, and dreams, are vain. The heart has fantasies like a woman in labor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.34.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:6",
      "text": "If they are not sent in a visitation from the Most High, don’t give your heart to them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.34.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:7",
      "text": "For dreams have led many astray. They have failed by putting their hope in them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.34.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:8",
      "text": "Without lying the law will be fulfilled. Wisdom is complete in a faithful mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.34.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:9",
      "text": "A well-instructed man knows many things. He who has much experience will declare understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.34.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:10",
      "text": "He who has no experience knows few things. But he who has traveled increases cleverness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.34.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:11",
      "text": "I have seen many things in my travels. My understanding is more than my words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.34.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:12",
      "text": "I was often in danger even to death. I was preserved because of these experiences.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.34.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:13",
      "text": "The spirit of those who fear the Lord will live, for their hope is in him who saves them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.34.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:14",
      "text": "Whoever fears the Lord won’t be afraid, and won’t be a coward, for he is his hope.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.34.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:15",
      "text": "Blessed is the soul of him who fears the Lord. To whom does he give heed? Who is his support?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.34.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:16",
      "text": "The eyes of the Lord are on those who love him, a mighty protection and strong support, a cover from the hot blast, a shade from the noonday sun, a guard from stumbling, and a help from falling.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.34.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:17",
      "text": "He raises up the soul, and enlightens the eyes. He gives health, life, and blessing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.34.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:18",
      "text": "He who sacrifices a thing wrongfully gotten, his offering is made in mockery. The mockeries of wicked men are not acceptable.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.34.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:19",
      "text": "The Most High has no pleasure in the offerings of the ungodly, Neither is he pacified for sins by the multitude of sacrifices.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.34.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:20",
      "text": "Like one who kills a son before his father’s eyes is he who brings a sacrifice from the goods of the poor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.34.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:21",
      "text": "The bread of the needy is the life of the poor. He who deprives him of it is a man of blood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.34.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:22",
      "text": "Like one who murders his neighbor is he who takes away his living. Like a shedder of blood is he who deprives a hireling of his hire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.34.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:23",
      "text": "When one builds, and another pulls down, what profit do they have but toil?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.34.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:24",
      "text": "When one prays, and another curses, whose voice will the Lord listen to?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.34.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:25",
      "text": "He who washes himself after touching a dead body, and touches it again, what does he gain by his washing?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.34.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:26",
      "text": "Even so a man fasting for his sins, and going again, and doing the same, who will listen to his prayer? What profit does he have in his humiliation?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
